[div class=p 
	"Supports similar syntax used by web search engines.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"					For more information, see the 
	[a href=https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/textsearch-controls.html#TEXTSEARCH-PARSING-QUERIES rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"postgres text parsing documentation
	]a
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The search is in-sensitive for spelling. For example, ‹
	[a class=intlink href=/Search?SearchTerms=megaman 
		"megaman
	]a
	"› and ‹
	[a class=intlink href=/Search?SearchTerms=Megaman 
		"Megaman
	]a
	"› give the same results.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"However, the search may be sensitive to spacing. For example, ‹
	[a class=intlink href=/Search?SearchTerms=mega+man 
		"mega man
	]a
	"› gives different result than ‹
	[a class=intlink href=/Search?SearchTerms=megaman 
		"megaman
	]a
	"›
	$LF
	"Much like the Google search, including more words in the search narrows down the search. ‹
	[a class=intlink href=/Search?SearchTerms=Metroid 
		"Metroid
	]a
	"› will find all Metroid-related articles and movies for all consoles, but ‹
	[a class=intlink href=/Search?SearchTerms=Super+Metroid 
		"Super Metroid
	]a
	"› will only find those which contain also the word ‹Super›.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"For exact phrase searching try the 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Advanced Search|href=/Search/Advanced)
	".
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If you don't find the results you're looking for, we suggest also trying a 
	[a href=https://www.google.com/search?q=site:tasvideos.org rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Google search
	]a
	".
]div
